comments:
Reproduced and isolated source pattern causing grief to SR2 JIT.

if replacing following code
...
unitScope.recordReference(unitScope.fPackage.compoundName, name);
Binding binding = unitScope.fPackage.getTypeOrPackage(name);
...

with following using an extra local variable 'currentPackage'
...
PackageBinding currentPackage = unitScope.fPackage;
unitScope.recordReference(currentPackage.compoundName, name);
Binding binding = currentPackage.getTypeOrPackage(name);

then it runs ok.

This is only a workaround for a JIT bug, but still interesting for users of SR2
...
